<exercise>
<p>The radius of a sphere is constantly changing. Find the radius of a
sphere when the rate of change of the surface area and the rate of
change of the volume are equal.</p>
</exercise>

<exercise>
<introduction>  <p>
    A ballon is rising vertically above a straight, level road at a
    constant rate of <m>5</m> ft/sec. When the balloon is <m>100</m> feet
    above the road a bicycle passes directly underneath moving at
    <m>30</m> ft/sec. 
  </p></introduction>
  <task>
    <p>
      How fast is the distance between them changing <m>10</m> seconds
      later?
    </p>
  </task>
<task>
<p>
How fast is the angle from directly below the balloon, to the ballon,
to the bicycle changing <m>10</m> seconds later?
</p>
</task>
<task>
<p>
Do parts
(a) and (b) again assuming that the ground is sloping upwards at <m>30^\circ</m>. 
</p>

</task>

</exercise>


